	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />From LCD to CRT I have not heard of any color display that used anything but RGB. Its technically possible different method could be used like maybe CMYK like what is used in printing but but if the pixels are not blending together it would not really matter, it would seem it was just not obvious or perhaps the pixelation you saw was due to the toy computer's output resolution being very low and not the screens actual pixel sizes.
<br />
<br />its simple enough to find out just get real close to the screen and you can see the individual colors

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


