	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In the city I live, the parking meters use a red/transparent LCD to indicate when they're expired. However, this is apparently a function of the polarizer, so you'd need a much more expensive assembly to get CMYK pixel blocks. 
<br />
<br />Also, the (many year old) color E-Ink prototypes I'd seen were arrays of CMYK dots. (It's kinda unfortunate, because you lose a lot of saturation)
<br />
<br />Have you seen the old liquid-crystal based thermometers? I've not seen them much recently. Or mood rings. Liquid crystal can change the color it selects for based on temperature or pressure.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


